TESDA TRAINERS METHODOLOGY - D7

CORE COMPETENCIES (PLAN TRAINING SESSION)

Identifying the Learner's TRaining REquirements
-Factors to consider in planning a training session
	>Language, Literacy and Numeracy (LL&N)
	>Cultural and Language Background
	>Education and General Knowledge
	>Gender
	>Age
	>Physical Ability
	>Previous experience with the topic
	>Previous learning experience
	>Training level completed
	>Special courses
	>Other needs


Learning stype could be either be visual, auditory, or kinesthetic

Visual Learners
-Preferes the use of pictures, maps, diagrams, drawings or illustrations
	to access and understand new information

Auditory Learners
-Best understand new content through listening and speaking situations such as
	lecture and group discussion

Kinesthetic Learner
-Are "hands-on" learners and learn best thru figuring things out by hand.
-Referred to as "hyperactive" learners with concentration issues

Trainees' Current Competencies
-Skills and knowledge of your trainees obtained through formal training, work, 
	or life experience.


How can be the Current Competencies be Determined
-Self-Assessment Checklink
	>checklist of competencies required of a qualification
-Proof of Comptetencies
	>employment, certificates, projects done by trainees, awards, 
	   and other related proofs
-Pre-assessment results


Why determione current competencies
-To identify the competencies to be covered in the session plan.
-To assess the trainee's current competency in comparison to the stated standards
	of competency required
-To identify which relevant skills the trainee possess and does not possess,
	so that the training program can be tailored accordingly


Factors to consider in using evidences submitted by a prospective trainee
	as a proof of his current competencies
-Authenticity of the document
-Date when the competencies were acquired
-Standing of the company/employer who issued the certificate


Tools/Instruments in Identifying Current Competencies

Current commpetencies are determined by using the following forms:
1. Self-assessment Check (Form 4.1)
2. Validation of Competency evidences (Form 4.2)
3. Summary of current competencies versus required competencies (Form 4.3)
4. Training Needs (Form 4.4)

